
Python is a high-level programming language used to develop software, websites, data analysis, and automation programs.

Key features:

 Easy to read & write (simple English-like syntax)

 Interpreted (no need to compile)

 High-level (no memory management needed)

 Object-oriented & procedural

 Large standard library

 Platform independent (Windows, Linux, macOS)

Uses of Python:

Web development (Django, Flask)

Data Science & AI

Automation & scripting

Machine Learning

Game development

Scientific computing